at-media-rule.content:
An @media rule
specifies the target [media types](#media-types) (separated
by commas) of a set of [statements](syndata.html#tokenization) (delimited by curly
braces). Invalid statements must be ignored per [4.1.7 "Rule sets, declaration blocks,
and selectors"](syndata.html#rule-sets) and [4.2
"Rules for handling parsing errors."](syndata.html#parsing-errors) The @media construct allows style
sheet rules for various media in the same style sheet:

```

 @media print {
 body { font-size: 10pt }
 }
 @media screen {
 body { font-size: 13px }
 }
 @media screen, print {
 body { line-height: 1.2 }
 }

```

Style rules outside of @media rules apply to all media types
that the style sheet applies to. At-rules inside @media are invalid in
CSS 2.2.
